  <walkingDescription><![CDATA[<p>The Canadian Rockies are renowned as a destination for hikers. The backcountry scenery from the network of more than 4,000km of marked trails is remarkable, giving you first hand views of sparkling lakes and glaciers, waterfalls and ancient forests. Wherever you stay there is a multitude of hiking options on your doorstep. Bow Falls, Tunnel Mountain and The Marsh Trail are popular walks from Banff.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Guided Interpretive Hikes | £50 (daily)</strong></p>
<p>Full programme of walks with professional guides. Includes transport, deluxe packed lunch, use of hiking poles and binoculars.</p>
<p>Can be booked locally in resort. Price shown for guidance only.</p>]]></walkingDescription>
